19 54 - 68 - 05. Records - Confidentiality - Disclosure - Penalty .
20 1. Identifiable information concerning an individual who is applying for or receiving public
21 services under this chapter is confidential and may be disclosed only:
22 a. In the administration of any program under the supervision or administration of
23 the office.
24 b. When authorized by a policy of the office.
25 c. When allowed or required by rule or law.
26 2. A report concerning an applicant, provider, or recipient of public services is confidential
27 if the report is made in good faith and may be disclosed only to:
28 a. Authorized staff and agents of the office, who may further disclose the
29 information to a person that has a definite interest in the well-being of the
30 individual concerned, is in a position to serve the individual's interests, and that
